6 A JOINT RESOLUTION OF THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE STATE OF
7 MONTANA APPLYING FOR A CONVENTION OF THE STATES UNDER ARTICLE V OF THE
8 CONSTITUTION OF THE UNITED STATES FOR THE PURPOSE OF PROPOSING AN AMENDMENT TO
9 THE CONSTITUTION TO SET TERM LIMITS ON MEMBERS OF CONGRESS.
10
11 WHEREAS, Article V of the Constitution of the United States provides the states with the authority to
12 call an amendment convention for the purpose of proposing an amendment to the Constitution of the United
13 States on application by at least two-thirds of the states; and
14 WHEREAS, this power provides the states with the leverage needed to force Congress to act when it
15 otherwise does not want to; and
16 WHEREAS, the citizens of Montana overwhelmingly support term limits on members of Congress; and
17 WHEREAS, the Legislature of the State of Montana hereby joins with other states in instructing
18 Congress to draft a term limits amendment and send it to the states for ratification, failing which the states will
19 act on their own; and
20 WHEREAS, the Montana Legislature, a body of citizen legislators, desires to restore rotation in office
21 for members serving in the United States Congress.
22
23 NOW, THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED BY THE SENATE AND THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF
24 THE STATE OF MONTANA:
25 (1) That pursuant to Article V of the Constitution of the United States, the Legislature of the State
26 of Montana formally applies to the United States Congress to call a convention limited to proposing an
27 amendment to the Constitution of the United States to set a limit on the number of terms a person may be
28 elected as a member of the United States House of Representatives and as a member of the United States
